tool.name: GDVSpectra_CVA

param.name: in_raw_nc_path
param.dialogReference:
A raw satellite data NetCDF generated by the COG Fetch module. Input NetCDF must have coordinates for x, y and time.

Three or more years worth of satellite imagery is required to run this tool.

param.name: in_mask_nc_path
param.displayname: Input GDV Threshold mask NetCDF file
param.dialogReference: A GDV Likelihood Threshold NetCDF generated by the GDV Threshold tool. The threshold areas act as a mask to reduce analysis down to high likelihood vegetation areas. Requires x, y and a threshold variable.

param.name: out_nc_path
param.dialogReference: The NetCDF file containing the CVA outputs. This output will always contain x, y, time coordinates and four variables indicating various magnitudes within four different change types.

param.name: in_base_start_year
param.dialogReference:
The start date of the baseline period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded. If more than one year provided for start and end baseline dates, a median of all images will be used. All comparison images will be compared to this baseline.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_base_end_year
param.dialogReference:
The end date of the baseline period. All satellite data after this date will be excluded. If more than one year provided for start and end baseline dates, a median of all images will be used. All comparison images will be compared to the user-defined baseline.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_comp_start_year
param.dialogReference:
The start date of the comparison period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded. Each year within the comparison start and end period will be compared to the same baseline separately.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_comp_end_year
param.dialogReference:
The end date of the comparison period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded. Each year within the comparison start and end period will be compared to the same baseline separately.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_analysis_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) to compare every year. If more than one month is selected, a median of these months is used.

Select all months to compare whole years, or several months to compare seasons. Three or more months recommended.

param.name: in_tmf
param.dialogReference:
The magnitude threshold factor (also known as threshold median factor). Used to calculate a threshold magnitude for which pixels are considered stable, i.e. no change.

The default value is 2 times the median non-zero magnitude.

param.name: in_stand_qupper
param.dialogReference:
The upper n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. Percentile is used as the maximum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produced optimal results.

param.name: in_stand_qlower
param.dialogReference:
The lower n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the minimum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_fmask_flags
param.expression: NoData | Valid | Cloud | Shadow | Snow | Water
param.dialogReference:
Pixel classes provided by the DEA Fmask algorithm. The DEA Landsat and Sentinel satellite image products come with a mask band to assist in removing clouds, shadow, nodata, etc. Only selected pixel classes shown here will be used in analysis, whilst all others will be masked out (and later interpolated).

The default values include Valid, Snow and Water classes, and all others are masked out.

param.name: in_max_cloud
param.dialogReference:
The maximum percentage of cloud cover allowed within a satellite image before it is discarded from analysis. A value of 0 will return all satellite data with no registered cloud cover.

As a general rule of thumb, the smaller your study area the lower this value should be. The default value is 10%.

param.name: in_interpolate
param.dialogReference:
If checked, linear interpolation is applied along the time dimension at each pixel of the input satellite image NetCDF so as to fill in missing pixels masked out via the DEA Fmask band.

The default is recommended.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the outputs of the tool on the currently active map.

tool.summary:
Generates a library of Change Vector Analysis (CVA) change maps using a raw satellite NetCDF file. This method takes a NetCDF of raw satellite imagery, calculates greenness and brightness data via the Tasselled Cap index, and compares every comparison image to a user-set baseline year(s).

The CVA technique calculates angle and magnitude of change vectors between two satellite images (i.e., a baseline vs a comparison image). From these angles, certain types of change can be isolated (e.g., angles between 90-180 degrees indicate bare soil/moisture increase or vegetation decline). Additionally, magnitude can be used to highlight the amount of change that occurred.

See citation: Chen, J., Gong, P., He, C., Pu, R. and Shi, P., 2003. Land-use/land-cover change detection using improved change-vector analysis. Photogrammetric Engineering & Remote Sensing, 69(4), pp.369-379.
